se.hig.dvg329.algomaze.control

Class MazeController

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.hig.dvg329.algomaze.control.MazeController

  • public class MazeController
extends java.lang.Object
    The MazeController class is responsible for handling the currently used Maze. The generateMaze(String) and solveMaze(String) methods are used to generate and solve Mazes, respectively. The MazeController class

    Thomas Lundgren

      • generateMaze

        public void generateMaze(java.lang.String algorithm)
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Generates a random Maze using the algorithm provided as the method's argument. This method will turn an empty Maze into a randomized perfect Maze. The Maze used is the Maze lastly created by calling the createMaze(int, int) method.
        Parameters:
        algorithm - the algorithm to be used to generate the Maze. The only implemented method currently is "Prim".
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an application tries to call this method with a String representing a not yet implemented algorithm as an argument.

      • solveMaze

        public void solveMaze(java.lang.String algorithm)
               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Solves a previously generated Maze.
        Parameters:
        algorithm - the algorithm to be used to solve the Maze. The only implemented algorithm so far is "Dijkstra".
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an application tries to call this method with a String representing a not yet implemented algorithm as an argument.

      • setGenerationTime

        public void setGenerationTime(double generationTime)

      • getGenerationTime

        public double getGenerationTime()
        Returns the time it took to generate the lastly generated Maze. DISCLAIMER: Note that all overhead operations are included in the generation time, it does not tell you how fast a particular algorithm is, but rather how fast it is in the context of this application. Note also that it should never be compared to maze solving times, since the overhead of these operations are different.
        Returns:
        the generation time of the lastly generated maze.

      • setSolvingTime

        public void setSolvingTime(double solvingTime)

      • getSolvingTime

        public double getSolvingTime()
        Returns the time it took to generate the lastly solved Maze. DISCLAIMER: Note that all overhead operations are included in the solving time, it does not tell you how fast a particular algorithm is, but rather how fast it is in the context of this application. Note also that it should never be compared to maze generation times, since the overhead of these operations are different.
        Returns:
        the solving time of the lastly solved maze.
